Police in Ekurhuleni have made a sweet arrest. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police in Ekurhuleni have made a sweet arrest. 13 suspects were arrested for selling counterfeit goods. READ: Police seize fake kits in international trafficking crackdown The arrest comes after police received a tip-off about expired sweets and chocolates being repackaged, to be sold to the communities through spaza shops. The suspects were apprehended at a warehouse in Springs, East of Johannesburg.